New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower
WELLINGTON , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- The New Zealand sharemarket closed lower here Monday .
The NZSE40 Index ended 16 points lower at 1719 with a turnover of 42 million NZ dollars ( 21 million U.S. dollars ) .
AMP was the only stock leading to gain , rising 41 cents to 2466 cents .
Fletcher Energy fell 20 cents to 300 cents , Telecom 11 cents to 727 cents , Fletcher Building 8 cents to 196 cents , and Carter Holt Harvey 2 cents to 130 cents .
Air New Zealand and Fletcher Paper dipped 1 cent each to 161 cents and 102 cents respectively , while Brierley Investments , Auckland Airport and Fletcher Forest closed stable at 49 cents , 185 cents and 56 cents respectively .
